location: Location Amundsen (Roald) Park 6200 W. Bloomingdale Ave. Chicago, IL 60639
description: Get ready for a vibrant Harvest Celebration at Amundsen Park! Join us for Artful Sips and Bingo Hits, an event designed to inspire your creativity and bring some friendly competition. Enjoy lively music as you explore your artistic side with painting. Then, get ready to shout "Bingo!" for a chance to win. It's the perfect way to celebrate the harvest season with friends and fun!

title: Community Bonfire at Oz
location: Location Oz Park 2021 N. Burling St. Chicago, IL 60614
description: See your local park in a new light! The Nature Oasis Community Bonfire Series invites community members to experience their park by firelight. Spend the evening in the park meeting your neighbors, learning about local wildlife and warming up next to a fire! Unfortunately we are not able to provide marshmallows just yet, but please feel welcome to bring your own and we will provide the roasting sticks. Join us within the first 15 minutes of the event for a brief lesson on campfire building.

description: Yoga, can help individuals decrease stress and increase their ability to focus and problem solve. First responders experience stress and trauma at higher levels than civilians. Please bring a yoga mat and wear comfortable clothing. Weather dependent.
